  "body": "I am just leaving this here in case you are interested:\r\n\r\nSo back when hardhat didnt ship yet I got an `invalid opcode` bug on buidler-ganache in forkmode for this code and especially for the [gelatoCore.unstakeExecutor()](https://github.com/gelatodigital/gelato-network/blob/master/contracts/gelato_core/GelatoExecutors.sol#L32) method. I believe the bug must have to do with the `Address.sendValue` method from OpenZeppelin. I think `buidler-ganache` gave me an `invalid opcode` for calls to that method elsewhere too.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n// running `npx buidler run` automatically makes use of buidler-waffle plugin\r\n// => only dependency we need is \"chai\"\r\nconst bre = require(\"@nomiclabs/buidler\");\r\nconst { ethers } = bre;\r\nconst GelatoCoreLib = require(\"@gelatonetwork/core\");\r\nconst { sleep } = GelatoCoreLib;\r\n\r\n(async function main() {\r\n  if (bre.network.name !== \"ganache\") {\r\n    console.error(\"Test Suite is meant to be run on ganache only\");\r\n    process.exit(1);\r\n  }\r\n  // ===== GELATO LOCAL SETUP ==================\r\n  const gelatoCore = await ethers.getContractAt(\r\n    GelatoCoreLib.GelatoCore.abi,\r\n    bre.network.config.GelatoCore\r\n  );\r\n\r\n  // DEBUG: buidler-ganache INVALID OPCODE bug\r\n\r\n  await gelatoCore.stakeExecutor({ value: ethers.utils.parseEther(\"2\") });\r\n\r\n  await gelatoCore.unstakeExecutor();\r\n\r\n  await sleep(20000);\r\n\r\n  // DEBUG END\r\n})();\r\n```\r\n\r\nBack then I talked to @alcuadrado and we assumed that it might be a ganache related bug.\r\n\r\nSo today I went back and tested the same code on hardhat:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n// running `npx hardhat run` automatically makes use of buidler-waffle plugin\r\nconst hre = require(\"hardhat\");\r\nconst { ethers } = hre;\r\nconst GelatoCoreLib = require(\"@gelatonetwork/core\");\r\nconst { sleep } = GelatoCoreLib;\r\n\r\n(async function main() {\r\n  if (hre.network.name !== \"hardhat\") {\r\n    console.error(\"Test Suite is meant to be run on hardhat only\");\r\n    process.exit(1);\r\n  }\r\n  // ===== GELATO LOCAL SETUP ==================\r\n  const gelatoCore = await ethers.getContractAt(\r\n    GelatoCoreLib.GelatoCore.abi,\r\n    hre.network.config.GelatoCore\r\n  );\r\n\r\n  // DEBUG: buidler-ganache INVALID OPCODE bug\r\n\r\n  // NO BUG on hardhat\r\n\r\n  await gelatoCore.stakeExecutor({ value: ethers.utils.parseEther(\"2\") });\r\n\r\n  await gelatoCore.unstakeExecutor();\r\n\r\n  await sleep(20000);\r\n\r\n  // DEBUG END\r\n})();\r\n```\r\n\r\n**And indeed, no `invalid opcode` bug was thrown for the [gelatoCore.unstakeExecutor()](https://github.com/gelatodigital/gelato-network/blob/6950d08229dc0a1ef25dc65dd40291bef3be09d9/contracts/gelato_core/GelatoExecutors.sol#L32) method.** \r\n\r\n**Yeaah! Hardhat is great!** ",
